In JavaScript, you can create an endpoint using a library like Express.js. Here's an example of creating a simple endpoint that responds with \Hello, World!\:\n\n```javascript\nconst express = require('express');\nconst app = express();\nconst port = 3000;\n\napp.get('/hello', (req, res) => {\n  res.send('Hello, World!');\n});\n\napp.listen(port, () => {\n  console.log(`Server running at http://localhost:${port}`);\n});\n```\n\nIn this example, we are creating a GET endpoint at `/hello` that responds with \Hello, World!\ when accessed.
